training_examples.input: What do you know about Solana Transaction Types?
training_examples.context: Solana supports multiple transaction types: System Program (account creation, SOL transfers), SPL Token Program (token transfers, minting, burning), Associated Token Account Program (ATA creation), Metaplex (NFT creation and metadata), Stake Program (staking operations), Vote Program (validator voting), and various DeFi protocols like Jupiter, Raydium, Orca, Marinade, and Kamino.
training_examples.expected_output: Solana supports multiple transaction types: System Program (account creation, SOL transfers), SPL Token Program (token transfers, minting, burning), Associated Token Account Program (ATA creation), Metaplex (NFT creation and metadata), Stake Program (staking operations), Vote Program (validator voting), and various DeFi protocols like Jupiter, Raydium, Orca, Marinade, and Kamino.

training_examples.input: What do you know about System Program Transactions?
training_examples.context: System Program handles core Solana operations: CreateAccount (requires lamports for rent exemption), Transfer (SOL transfers between accounts), Allocate (space allocation), Assign (program assignment), CreateAccountWithSeed (deterministic account creation), and TransferWithSeed (transfers from seeded accounts).
training_examples.expected_output: System Program handles core Solana operations: CreateAccount (requires lamports for rent exemption), Transfer (SOL transfers between accounts), Allocate (space allocation), Assign (program assignment), CreateAccountWithSeed (deterministic account creation), and TransferWithSeed (transfers from seeded accounts).

training_examples.input: What do you know about SPL Token Operations?
training_examples.context: SPL Token Program enables: Token transfers (with optional multisig), Minting new tokens (requires mint authority), Burning tokens (reduces supply), Approving delegates (allows third parties to transfer), Freezing accounts (pauses transfers), Thawing accounts (resumes transfers), and setting authorities (transferring control).
training_examples.expected_output: SPL Token Program enables: Token transfers (with optional multisig), Minting new tokens (requires mint authority), Burning tokens (reduces supply), Approving delegates (allows third parties to transfer), Freezing accounts (pauses transfers), Thawing accounts (resumes transfers), and setting authorities (transferring control).

training_examples.input: What do you know about DEX Trading Strategies?
training_examples.context: Profitable DEX strategies include: Arbitrage between Raydium and Orca pools, triangular arbitrage (SOLUSDCBONKSOL), cross-protocol arbitrage (Jupiter vs direct pools), sandwich attacks (MEV), back-running profitable transactions, liquidation sniping, and new pool sniping on launch.
training_examples.expected_output: Profitable DEX strategies include: Arbitrage between Raydium and Orca pools, triangular arbitrage (SOLUSDCBONKSOL), cross-protocol arbitrage (Jupiter vs direct pools), sandwich attacks (MEV), back-running profitable transactions, liquidation sniping, and new pool sniping on launch.

training_examples.input: What do you know about Flash Loans on Solana?
training_examples.context: Flash loans on Solana: Kamino provides decentralized flash loans for arbitrage, liquidation, and refinancing. Solend offers flash loans for various DeFi operations. Port Finance supports flash loans with credit delegation. Flash loans must be borrowed and repaid in the same transaction - perfect for atomic arbitrage where the arbitrage profit covers the loan fee.
training_examples.expected_output: Flash loans on Solana: Kamino provides decentralized flash loans for arbitrage, liquidation, and refinancing. Solend offers flash loans for various DeFi operations. Port Finance supports flash loans with credit delegation. Flash loans must be borrowed and repaid in the same transaction - perfect for atomic arbitrage where the arbitrage profit covers the loan fee.

training_examples.input: What do you know about MEV Strategies?
training_examples.context: MEV (Miner Extractable Value) on Solana: Front-running (detecting large pending swaps and buying before them), back-running (following profitable transactions), sandwich attacks (buying before and selling after a large trade), liquidation extraction (being first to liquidate underwater positions), arbitrage extraction (capturing price differences), and time-bandit attacks (manipulating timestamp-dependent logic).
training_examples.expected_output: MEV (Miner Extractable Value) on Solana: Front-running (detecting large pending swaps and buying before them), back-running (following profitable transactions), sandwich attacks (buying before and selling after a large trade), liquidation extraction (being first to liquidate underwater positions), arbitrage extraction (capturing price differences), and time-bandit attacks (manipulating timestamp-dependent logic).

training_examples.input: What do you know about Jupiter Aggregator?
training_examples.context: Jupiter is Solana's premier DEX aggregator supporting: Multi-hop routing (up to 3 hops), split trades across multiple routes, real-time quote updates, transaction bundling, and MEV protection. Jupiter integrates with Raydium, Orca, Whirlpool, Aldrin, and many other AMMs. Use Jupiter for optimal price execution and slippage protection.

training_examples.input: What do you know about Raydium AMM?

training_examples.input: What do you know about Marinade Staking?
